The beginning course of Finnish: basic vocabulary and grammar, practical conversational language.
Topics covered: 
greeting, presenting oneself, personal information, politeness expressions; asking for price, numerals (cardinal and ordinal numbers), colours, most common adjectives, clothing; seasons, months, weekdays, time and hours, weather; family, home, place of living; possessive suffixes, declinable word stem, verb conversion in the present tense.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course provides students with basic knowledge of conversational Finnish. After passing the course, the student knows how to use Finnish grammar and vocabulary necessary for everyday interaction.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student:  1) knows the main Finnish grammar rules; 2) can understand phrases and the highest frequency vocabulary related to areas of most immediate personal relevance (family, shopping, home, work); 3) can read short, simple texts; 4) can find specific predictable information in simple everyday texts; 5) can communicate in simple and routine situations; 6) can use a series of phrases and sentences to describe in simple terms his/her family and other people, living conditions, educational background and job; 7) can use relevant sources of information (dictionaries and handbooks, the Internet).
